120
00:14:32,748 --> 00:14:35,369
Very brief overview for people who aren't familiar with the program.

121
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:38,691
Community Development Block Grant is distributed through the U.S.

122
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,352
Department of Housing and Urban Development.

123
00:14:40,832 --> 00:14:42,954
City of Medford is considered an entitlement community.

124
00:14:43,014 --> 00:14:49,337
Basically, that means that we have a population of over 50,000 based on the age of our housing, our citizens, and poverty.

125
00:14:49,357 --> 00:14:52,959
There's a formula application and the city's eligible to apply for that money.

126
00:14:53,670 --> 00:15:02,975
Part of the requirements of submitting and receiving that money is to do an annual action plan, and then every five years to do a five-year plan.

127
00:15:02,995 --> 00:15:03,975
So this year we're doing both.

128
00:15:04,035 --> 00:15:07,457
We did a five-year plan, and we also are doing the one-year action plan.

129
00:15:07,897 --> 00:15:16,622
We've had a process that's been a little bit different this year, and HUD is a little bit slow, but it's moving toward entering the digital era.

130
00:15:17,143 --> 00:15:22,613
and has basically required us to use a new, it's called the econ planning suite.

131
00:15:23,034 --> 00:15:28,545
So we'll be submitting that in addition to using our normal financial software that we use through HUD.

132
00:15:29,093 --> 00:15:34,055
We have done a regional planning process on housing with the North Suburban Consortium.

133
00:15:34,095 --> 00:15:35,776
There have been some regional meetings on that.

134
00:15:36,276 --> 00:15:42,558
And in addition, we have also done consultations with a number of agencies to identify what their needs are.

135
00:15:42,579 --> 00:15:47,641
A lot of public service agencies that you're familiar with and general information meetings.

136
00:15:47,661 --> 00:15:56,044
We also had the council meeting committee of the whole to allow the public service agencies recently to speak about their needs and their requests for applications that they funded.

137
00:15:56,498 --> 00:15:59,921
So I won't take too much of your time, but I will come back and answer any questions that you have.

138
00:16:01,002 --> 00:16:05,105
And in general, the city's identifying their housing and community development needs.

139
00:16:06,106 --> 00:16:09,148
It is fairly specific because the funding source is specific.

140
00:16:09,208 --> 00:16:14,793
So we're really focusing here in HUD on benefits to low and moderate income citizens.

141
00:16:15,253 --> 00:16:17,315
And that's the primary purpose of this program.

142
00:16:17,815 --> 00:16:21,899
It's not, you know, general use of government funds.

143
00:16:21,979 --> 00:16:32,288
It's targeted and to attempt to revitalize neighborhoods that are not deteriorating and to assist low and moderate income people with jobs and social services and housing needs.

144
00:16:32,328 --> 00:16:33,690
And that's what we do here in this plan.

145
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:38,374
And the city council, the past five years, we have worked together to fund

146
00:16:38,852 --> 00:16:46,157
and implement over $7 million worth of public projects and facility improvements and public service agencies.

147
00:16:46,197 --> 00:16:56,103
So we've had quite an accomplishment with our joint efforts to serve the citizens of the city of Medford who are low and moderate income and we're a working class community.

148
00:16:56,123 --> 00:16:57,644
The funds are very important to us.

149
00:16:57,684 --> 00:16:59,245
They also supplement the general

150
00:16:59,766 --> 00:17:02,348
city budget in terms of the delivery of services.

151
00:17:02,408 --> 00:17:08,452
So we've been very successful in forging this partnership, and I hope that we can continue to do that.

152
00:17:08,872 --> 00:17:12,034
This year, we're applying for $1,433,774.

153
00:17:13,755 --> 00:17:17,497
First time we've had really a nominal cut in CDBG funds.

154
00:17:17,998 --> 00:17:20,619
It's approximately $6,000 less than we got last year.

155
00:17:20,699 --> 00:17:21,540
So that's good.

156
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:25,643
We've been having a steady cut in federal funding.

157
00:17:25,683 --> 00:17:28,985
So this is a nominal decrease, which has been great.

158
00:17:30,515 --> 00:17:34,777
Generally, we've developed some housing goals, and our one and five-year goals are fairly consistent.

159
00:17:35,678 --> 00:17:37,219
We address housing.

160
00:17:37,259 --> 00:17:45,103
Now, there's a small amount of money that we're proposing in this budget for housing, but we do have some money for prior years, about $250,000 of prior year money in housing.

161
00:17:45,463 --> 00:17:48,745
And we are also eligible to apply through the North Suburban Consortium.

162
00:17:49,125 --> 00:17:58,931
And generally, what we do in that case is we use some of the money for administrative costs when we're working with developers who have received, for instance, Medford Community Housing as a local group

163
00:17:59,447 --> 00:18:05,771
who has applied for funding through the consortium and we've assisted them with CDBG funds in the past and with getting home funds.

164
00:18:06,311 --> 00:18:09,533
So we do regional housing and we also do some local housing efforts.

165
00:18:10,634 --> 00:18:15,957
The general goals on housing are to enhance the conditions and quality of life for low income residents.

166
00:18:16,397 --> 00:18:25,223
We also work with public housing residents and with the housing authority in order to make sure that there are proper referrals for people so that they find themselves in a situation where they are

167
00:18:25,744 --> 00:18:32,487
approaching homelessness or they're on a waiting list, we try to work with them also to coordinate the efforts to make sure that they're properly housed.

168
00:18:33,787 --> 00:18:38,229
We assist and potentially fund non-profit housing developers in identifying development sites.

169
00:18:38,269 --> 00:18:40,410
I gave you an example of that with Medford Community Housing.

170
00:18:40,710 --> 00:18:41,930
They have no project this year.

171
00:18:42,190 --> 00:18:44,051
They have one currently with Main Street.

172
00:18:44,291 --> 00:18:46,652
We have no specific project identified for next year.

173
00:18:47,082 --> 00:18:51,085
But if they come forth with a property and we're able to assist them, then we will try to do that.

174
00:18:51,805 --> 00:18:54,227
And we administer general housing activities.

175
00:18:54,747 --> 00:19:02,052
We also have, you know, we have the ability to work and coordinate with all of our public sister agencies that are working on housing.

176
00:19:02,112 --> 00:19:04,253
We do a lot of referrals to people who have housing needs.

177
00:19:04,693 --> 00:19:08,596
We're not experts, but we will find an answer if we can.

178
00:19:08,656 --> 00:19:13,239
And we'll work with people who have the resources to address people's problems, housing problems, I should say.

179
00:19:14,152 --> 00:19:19,296
The second area that we fund as a goal is physical improvements to city systems and public facilities.

180
00:19:19,356 --> 00:19:24,440
