02:01:34,548 --> 02:01:38,129
Be it resolved that the position of Mayor of the City of Medford be discussed.

1604
02:01:38,489 --> 02:01:39,209
Councilor Penta.

1605
02:01:39,599 --> 02:01:41,700
Mr. President, this is a very important position.

1606
02:01:41,760 --> 02:01:51,226
As we all know, this will be the first time in so many, many years that this office is going to be vacated by the incumbent mayor, Michael McGlynn.

1607
02:01:51,507 --> 02:01:55,449
As I said before, I wish him well for whatever endeavor he so chooses.

1608
02:01:55,509 --> 02:02:00,112
And I would hope that he would be finishing out his term and not leaving ahead of time.

1609
02:02:00,172 --> 02:02:02,594
But be that as it may, that's not the issue.

1610
02:02:03,334 --> 02:02:09,158
Right now, the second highest position in this building, which is the Director of Budget and Personnel, has made an announcement.

1611
02:02:09,895 --> 02:02:12,936
that that individual is going to run and seek the office of mayor.

1612
02:02:13,336 --> 02:02:17,637
I believe that was done some seven days, six days after the mayor made his announcement.

1613
02:02:18,597 --> 02:02:21,038
And I believe that was on April 20th.

1614
02:02:21,658 --> 02:02:34,501
And as a result of that, a further announcement has been forthcoming as it relates to that individual now going to relinquish that position on May 15th.

1615
02:02:34,881 --> 02:02:38,482
And today, I believe we received another press release, which was dated April 21st.

1616
02:02:39,912 --> 02:02:49,937
as it relates to the fact that the Director of Budget and Personnel is going to be leaving effective May 15th, even though the announcement was made on April 20th.

1617
02:02:50,797 --> 02:02:57,861
In the second comment of the letter that states, I would not want the Office of Mayor to encounter any appearance of any conflict of interest.

1618
02:02:57,921 --> 02:02:59,682
And I think there is a, a, a miss there.

1619
02:02:59,722 --> 02:03:00,942
It's not the Office of Mayor.

1620
02:03:00,982 --> 02:03:04,684
I think it would be the Office of the Budget Director because unfortunately,

1621
02:03:05,373 --> 02:03:13,255
This individual is the one that presents the budget to the city council and goes through all the finances to make the city's council's budget come forward.

1622
02:03:13,776 --> 02:03:18,197
At the same time, it's also the person that's in charge of personnel.

1623
02:03:19,097 --> 02:03:25,399
There's only been one person that I've been able to find in the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, and the person comes from the city of Medford.

1624
02:03:26,300 --> 02:03:34,222
And when this person, many, many years ago, made his announcement that he was running for attorney general, he resigned his position as vice chairman

1625
02:03:35,098 --> 02:03:40,281
of the Ways and Means Committee of the State House, that was George L. Sacco, former representative George Sacco.

1626
02:03:41,241 --> 02:03:51,906
And that always stuck out in my mind when somebody running for jobs of such high authority, if you're going to be that committed to it, they relinquish their position, at-present position.

1627
02:03:51,946 --> 02:03:55,488
In that time, vice chairman of Ways and Means was a very important position.

1628
02:03:56,269 --> 02:03:59,190
But when he resigned that position, that was the day he made his announcement.

1629
02:03:59,850 --> 02:04:03,092
And I would personally believe, and I would think, and I would hope,

1630
02:04:03,782 --> 02:04:08,785
that a budget director would reconsider her position and resign immediately.

1631
02:04:09,446 --> 02:04:29,980
To have the luxury of reviewing a budget right now ahead of time or getting prepared for it, and I believe that the new person taking the budget director's place is now the procurement officer, and she will be assuming the budget director's position effective three days after May 15th, I think the conflict of interest is sort of like outstanding.

1632
02:04:30,020 --> 02:04:33,642
That's an undue advantage ahead of time of any other candidate that might be running

1633
02:04:33,938 --> 02:04:39,862
for that position, and in all fairness to all parties concerned, I think May 15th doesn't serve any purpose.

1634
02:04:39,903 --> 02:04:55,454
I think it needs to be done immediately in all fairness, because if in fact, if in fact, that person were to become elected mayor of the community, and that person would be working with a mayor, I would strike that, would be working with a budget in advance that no one else would have had that advantage, advantage point two.

1635
02:04:56,175 --> 02:05:00,298
So with that being said, with all due respect, I understand the position she's in.

1636
02:05:00,806 --> 02:05:04,708
I understand that she's the budget director, and also the budget director in charge of personnel.

1637
02:05:05,348 --> 02:05:15,452
And if I'm looking at the second press release that was offered here today, it says that the procurement officer will only assume the position of a budget director, but not of personnel.

1638
02:05:15,912 --> 02:05:17,693
So I guess there'll be an addendum.

1639
02:05:18,433 --> 02:05:20,654
Someone is going to pick up that position in the future.

1640
02:05:21,274 --> 02:05:28,757
So with that being said, I would like that position to be made loud and clear, and all fairness to all candidates, whoever they may be, he or she,

1641
02:05:29,632 --> 02:05:47,562
that if the second highest position in this city has that authority for which that person has in here, I think in all fairness, they should be resigning immediately, not till May 15th, to get their ducks in order, just in case that person does, in fact, become the mayor of this city.

1642
02:05:48,142 --> 02:05:48,803
And you know something?

1643
02:05:49,043 --> 02:05:54,606
I've spoken to members up in the State House, and they have basically said the same thing.

1644
02:05:55,066 --> 02:05:56,667
Judge Sacco set the precedent.

1645
02:05:57,205 --> 02:06:02,109
of resigning his position when he decided to run for Attorney General, because that's how committed he was.

1646
02:06:02,530 --> 02:06:07,514
He was willing to give up that for which he had to go forward and campaign for that position of Attorney General.

1647
02:06:08,115 --> 02:06:10,997
And that's what stuck out in my mind all these years.

1648
02:06:11,057 --> 02:06:19,205
And then when I saw the situation taking place here right now, and reading today's press release, I just thought that that would probably be the fair way to go.

1649
02:06:19,225 --> 02:06:23,869
And fairness to the person herself, to just leave

1650
02:06:24,337 --> 02:06:26,479
and move forward because you've already committed to a date.

1651
02:06:26,539 --> 02:06:27,920
Why did you commit on May 15th?

1652
02:06:28,000 --> 02:06:33,044
I don't know if it's to get the budget in order and hands it down to the next president.

1653
02:06:33,344 --> 02:06:38,608
Again, totally unfair and big advantage and a big conflict as far as I'm concerned.

1654
02:06:39,469 --> 02:06:40,209
Councilor Camuso.

1655
02:06:40,489 --> 02:06:41,830
Thank you, Mr. President.

1656
02:06:42,691 --> 02:06:45,994
I respectfully disagree with Councilor Penta.

1657
02:06:46,234 --> 02:06:53,499
I have had the honor and the distinct pleasure to serve with the lady in question on this city council and have been through several budgets with her.

1658
02:06:54,941 --> 02:06:59,304
She has the utmost integrity of high caliber.

1659
02:06:59,904 --> 02:07:04,387
And I am sure that she's doing what is right according to the law.

1660
02:07:04,987 --> 02:07:10,411
And if she feels that resigning on May 15th is the way to go, then I support it wholeheartedly.

1661
02:07:11,652 --> 02:07:16,015
I just, like I said, I just, the utmost integrity this woman has.

1662
02:07:16,115 --> 02:07:20,617
So I just respectfully disagree with my council colleague, and I'll leave it at that.

1663
02:07:21,818 --> 02:07:22,919
Thank you, Councilor Camuso.

1664
02:07:23,588 --> 02:07:27,191
So, we have really no motion before us except that there be a discussion.

1665
02:07:27,211 --> 02:07:28,392
Mr. President.

1666
02:07:28,412 --> 02:07:29,273
So, Councilor Penta.

1667
02:07:29,353 --> 02:07:35,197
Yes, in response to Councilor Camuso, I didn't challenge her integrity and I didn't challenge her high caliber.

1668
02:07:35,538 --> 02:07:39,341
What I'm saying is the potentiality of a conflict of interest existing.

1669
02:07:40,381 --> 02:07:44,265
I have, I hear what you're saying and I don't disagree with you.

1670
02:07:44,845 --> 02:07:47,047
But I'm more concerned about the appearance of a conflict.

1671
02:07:48,088 --> 02:07:49,649
Second highest position in this building.

1672
02:07:50,630 --> 02:07:52,251
That's how I'm looking at it right now.

1673
02:07:52,810 --> 02:07:56,292
Well, as just a little quick follow-up, and I'm going to let it go, Mr. President.

1674
02:07:57,593 --> 02:08:04,978
I'm sure, and I haven't had any conversations with her since she announced to be a candidate for mayor.

1675
02:08:05,479 --> 02:08:15,506
And I am sure, knowing her and the input and just the way she goes about her every day doing her job, she is doing it within the confines of the law.

1676
02:08:16,426 --> 02:08:20,889
And I have no question about anything as it relates to this matter.

1677
02:08:22,114 --> 02:08:28,658
I'm not ready to take any type of vote on this other than to just say, I'm just letting my feelings be known.

1678
02:08:29,799 --> 02:08:30,639
Madam Vice President.

1679
02:08:30,879 --> 02:08:32,740
Thank you, President de la Rousseau.

1680
02:08:33,541 --> 02:08:35,962
I just don't believe this is in our purview either.

1681
02:08:36,022 --> 02:08:41,726
I feel like, I think she did announce that she was going to resign this Thursday.

1682
02:08:42,886 --> 02:08:50,591
We don't know the reasoning for staying on two more weeks, but there has to be some sort of reason, whether it's to train somebody who's going to

1683
02:08:50,927 --> 02:08:54,110
be taking our place or at least taking our place for the June budget.

1684
02:08:54,531 --> 02:08:57,674
There has to be a reasoning that we're not aware of.

1685
02:08:58,314 --> 02:09:05,822
I think it's up to those running for mayor or for elected office or for taking a vote individually to protect their own conflict of interest.

1686
02:09:05,922 --> 02:09:07,584
It's really not in our purview.

1687
02:09:12,406 --> 02:09:13,587
Thank you, Councillor Lungo.

1688
02:09:14,087 --> 02:09:16,368
I too feel as though Ms.

1689
02:09:16,408 --> 02:09:22,951
